INSERT INTO `projects` VALUES (6,'Newmarket Racecourse','Newmarket Racecourse','2009-07-06 07:47:23','2009-08-21 15:06:13','newm.jpg','image/jpeg',61408,'2009-07-06 07:48:06','newm.jpg','image/jpeg',49500,'2009-07-08 14:16:18'),(7,'Titchwell Manor','Titchwell Manor is renowned for its food - especially its range of local produce. Rooms in the main house are done in muted Farrow & Ball washes, the general atmosphere and comfort of the furniture allows you to fully enjoy the fantastic range of food to hand.\r\n\r\nLloyd Loom of Spalding helped Titchwell Manor to bolster not only the comfort of their dining areas, but also the style of the rooms by providing furniture with specific Farrow and Ball finishes.\r\n\r\nWells - Bistro Tables\r\n','2009-07-06 07:51:12','2009-08-11 11:05:56','Titchwell.jpg','image/jpeg',181691,'2009-08-11 10:31:41','titch.jpg','image/jpeg',49509,'2009-07-08 14:15:59'),(9,'The George and Dragon','Situated between picturesque Coggeshall and Kelvedon the George & Dragon sets a new standard in value for money dining. The bar, layout and furnishings create a fresh and modern atmosphere to relax and dine in.\r\n\r\nLloyd Loom of Spalding furnished the George and Dragon with a range of contemporary furniture to compliment the feel of the bar and restaurant area.\r\n\r\nZeus - Neusis - Riverside - Delos','2009-07-06 07:52:39','2009-08-11 08:35:32','GandD.jpg','image/jpeg',94167,'2009-07-06 09:24:16','app.jpg','image/jpeg',45986,'2009-07-08 14:15:01'),(10,'Chatsworth House','Chatsworth is the home of the Duke and Duchess of Devonshire, one of Britain\'s best loved historic estates and the heart beat of the Peak District National Park. With famous works of art, a working farmyard, spectacular fountains and the finest shopping and eating, there is something for everyone to enjoy.\r\n\r\nChatsworth House has long upheld the notions of elegance and grace that run through the history of both the estate and Lloyd Loom production. Lloyd Loom of Spalding are proud to supple the Chatsworth Farm Shop with commercial and comfortable seating for their customers.','2009-07-06 07:53:25','2009-07-08 14:24:42','Chatsworth.jpg','image/jpeg',138476,'2009-07-06 09:04:12','chats.jpg','image/jpeg',54936,'2009-07-08 14:14:45'),(11,'Tresco Estate','There is an island of uncompromising beauty, hidden away from the tourists gaze. An island with a temperate climate and beautiful sea – a secluded haven of hills, coves and sandy beaches. \r\n\r\nTresco estate, and more recently Tresco\'s Flying Boat Club have supplied their customers with the highest quality seating avaliable in British Production today. The quality and stylings of the furntiure are mirrored in the beauty of the island and crystal sea that surrounds it.','2009-07-06 07:53:56','2009-07-08 14:20:17','Tresco.jpg','image/jpeg',117906,'2009-07-06 09:37:42','tresc.jpg','image/jpeg',45156,'2009-07-08 14:12:09'),(12,'Sa Taronja','The Sa Taronja Cultural Association in Andratx, Majorca has a variety of our furniture mostly in the Limon y Chelo restaurant.\r\n\r\nThere is a mixture of Boleros, Bantams, Belvoirs and Bistros arranged around Bistro tables in a delicious Mediterranean courtyard setting.    They are mostly in “Bracken” and “Fawn” and look wonderful in the dappled sunshine or evening candlelight.   The giant Babbington sofa with its bright green cushions is a popular resting place by the bar.\r\n','2009-07-06 07:54:29','2009-07-29 13:27:45','Sataro.jpg','image/jpeg',95397,'2009-07-06 09:44:42','sa.jpg','image/jpeg',49443,'2009-07-08 14:14:31'),(14,'Stockport Plaza','The Stockport Plaza Variety Theatre and Super Cinema\r\n\r\nA grand title for what is, without a doubt a very grand building. The Stockport Plaza Variety Theatre and Super Cinema is a magnificent example of a type once found in every town and has been restored as a labour of love to its original purpose making it the last of its kind in the UK.\r\n\r\nThe cafe/restaurant has been meticulously brought back to life using old photos and the original furniture tracked down with the help of Lloyd Loom of Spalding.    They have made 200 new chairs in the Spalding factory which almost exactly match the originals from the 1930s - even the colour used, “Naples Green”, is from an original Lloyd Loom formulation.\r\n\r\nHand made British furniture one of the many details that have contributed to this projects success.\r\n','2010-07-05 13:32:13','2010-07-07 10:11:55','Stockport.jpg','image/jpeg',231061,'2010-07-05 13:32:12','Stockport.jpg','image/jpeg',56184,'2010-07-07 10:11:55'),(15,'Thomson','Working with interior designers, SoHo Projects, our latest naturals weave has shown to be a huge success in the contract market as we furnish the breakout area at the new Luton home of TUK and Ireland.\r\n\r\nThe 16 custom-made 2 seater Madrid sofas along with 18 chairs, cube coffee tables and cube stools, all upholstered in burnt oak weave caused quite a stir when they were installed. The fabric, from Sekers, in bright colours compliments the furniture perfectly and helps to create a vibrant, lively atmosphere.\r\n\r\nThe unique pre dyed weave, that was only introduced only recently, has proved to be ideal for contract situations due to its hard wearing properties and we are all excited about the future possibility.\r\n','2010-07-12 07:53:32','2010-09-29 15:00:42','Thompson.jpg','image/jpeg',173526,'2010-07-12 07:53:31','tui.jpg','image/jpeg',73043,'2010-07-12 07:53:31');
